      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object obj)
        Used to compare two accounts.
        Overrides:
        equals in class Object
        Returns:
        true if two accounts are equal. Two accounts are equal if they have the same id, same projectid, same name (Configurationname), same accountname(Loginname), same server, same protocol, same password and the same flag to delete mails after seen.

      • isAnswerAccount

        public boolean isAnswerAccount()
        The answer account means that the incoming mail is checked whether there's an appropriate mail in a system. It's useful if the mail is answered from an external operator(the answer with cc or bcc is sent to the system).
        was:
        isAntwortkonto

      • setAnswerAccount

        public void setAnswerAccount(boolean answerAccount)
        Sets whether the account is an answer account. It's checked whether the fetched mail is an answer to the existing mail. In this case the both mails are completed. The mail was answered from external operator.
        was:
        setAntwortkonto
